{"repo": "birdnet-team/BirdNET-Analyzer", "pull_number": 801, "instance_id": "birdnet-team__BirdNET-Analyzer-801", "issue_numbers": [800], "base_commit": "6d86bec3ed02ddaac3301890ea7154d96740b596", "patch": "diff --git a/birdnet_analyzer/utils.py b/birdnet_analyzer/utils.py\nindex 72d9ea89..49fe9804 100644\n--- a/birdnet_analyzer/utils.py\n+++ b/birdnet_analyzer/utils.py\n@@ -440,7 +440,7 @@ def ensure_model_exists(check_perch: bool = False):\n \n     os.makedirs(checkpoint_dir, exist_ok=True)\n \n-    url = \"https://tuc.cloud/index.php/s/3BsizWy5M7CtQ5w/download/V2.4.zip\"\n+    url = \"https://tuc.cloud/index.php/s/886x39f5N3sdsAM/download/V2.4.zip\"\n     download_path = os.path.join(checkpoint_dir, \"V2.4.zip\")\n \n     response = requests.get(url, stream=True, timeout=30)\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Url for model download is broken\n# ValueError: Failed to download model file (Status code: 404) when running inference\n\n## Description\n\nI'm encountering an error when trying to run inference after installing BirdNET-Analyzer as a Python package following the documentation.\n\n## Steps to Reproduce\n\n1. Cloned the repository\n2. Ran `pip install .`\n3. Attempted to run inference with:\n```bash\n   python -m birdnet_analyzer.analyze <some-audio-file.wav>\n\n\nFile \"/home/tommasopellegrino/isacco/BirdNET-Analyzer/birdnet_analyzer/utils.py\", line 459, in ensure_model_exists\n    raise ValueError(f\"Failed to download the file. Status code: {response.status_code}\")\nValueError: Failed to download the file. Status code: 404\n```\n\nCan you update the url to point to a valid .zip of the model? Thanks\n\n", "hints_text": "I can confirm the issue\n\n", "all_hints_text": "I can confirm the issue\nThanks for reporting, the link is updated in the current repo\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/birdnet-team/BirdNET-Analyzer/commit/dfca82776f995a3e366d0f57da50eb3c1d0ab544"], "created_at": "2025-10-01T09:45:09Z"}
{"repo": "birdnet-team/BirdNET-Analyzer", "pull_number": 869, "instance_id": "birdnet-team__BirdNET-Analyzer-869", "issue_numbers": [862], "base_commit": "a5a9e1dae52736c6811842ad23317004404d7870", "patch": "diff --git a/pyproject.toml b/pyproject.toml\nindex 8e7ba872..42895ce7 100644\n--- a/pyproject.toml\n+++ b/pyproject.toml\n@@ -38,7 +38,7 @@ train = [\"keras-tuner\"]\n server = [\"bottle\", \"requests\"]\n gui = [\n     \"birdnet-analyzer[train,embeddings]\",\n-    \"gradio>=5.46\",\n+    \"gradio>=5.46, <6.0\",\n     \"pywebview>=6.0\",\n     \"pyobjc-framework-UniformTypeIdentifiers;platform_system=='Darwin'\", # macOS only, until pywebview adds it as dependency\n     \"plotly[express]\",\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "TypeError: Audio.__init__() got an unexpected keyword argument 'show_download_button'\n**Describe the bug**\nGUI can not be started.\n\n**To Reproduce**\n1. git checkout v2.4.0 (main also didn't work)\n2. pip install -e .[gui]\n3. birdnet-gui\n4. Error:\n\n```sh\n$ birdnet-gui \nModel found!\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"/home/stefan/Code/BirdNET-Analyzer/.venv312/bin/birdnet-gui\", line 8, in <module>\n    sys.exit(main())\n             ^^^^^^\n  File \"/home/stefan/Code/BirdNET-Analyzer/birdnet_analyzer/gui/__init__.py\", line 8, in main\n    gu.open_window(\n  File \"/home/stefan/Code/BirdNET-Analyzer/birdnet_analyzer/gui/utils.py\", line 850, in open_window\n    map_plots.extend(build() for build in builder)\n  File \"/home/stefan/Code/BirdNET-Analyzer/birdnet_analyzer/gui/utils.py\", line 850, in <genexpr>\n    map_plots.extend(build() for build in builder)\n                     ^^^^^^^\n  File \"/home/stefan/Code/BirdNET-Analyzer/birdnet_analyzer/gui/single_file.py\", line 127, in build_single_analysis_tab\n    segment_audio = gr.Audio(autoplay=True, type=\"numpy\", show_download_button=True, show_label=False, editable=False, visible=False)\n                    ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n  File \"/home/stefan/Code/BirdNET-Analyzer/.venv312/lib/python3.12/site-packages/gradio/component_meta.py\", line 194, in wrapper\n    return fn(self, **kwargs)\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\nTypeError: Audio.__init__() got an unexpected keyword argument 'show_download_button'\n```\n\n**Expected behavior**\nGUI opens\n\n**Desktop**\n - OS: Ubuntu\n - Version 24.10\n\n", "hints_text": "Hello,\n\nThe issue is the gradio version in the pyproject.toml, the quick fix is to change the line 41 to:\n    `\"gradio>=5.46,<6.0\",`\nThen you have to reinstall gradio with the commands `pip uninstall gradio` type `y` to uninstall and run the installer again `pip install .[gui]`\nThere incompatibility with gradio 6 it seems\n\n\n", "all_hints_text": "Hello,\n\nThe issue is the gradio version in the pyproject.toml, the quick fix is to change the line 41 to:\n    `\"gradio>=5.46,<6.0\",`\nThen you have to reinstall gradio with the commands `pip uninstall gradio` type `y` to uninstall and run the installer again `pip install .[gui]`\nThere incompatibility with gradio 6 it seems\n\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/birdnet-team/BirdNET-Analyzer/commit/0468474c79c46b1bec46b0dfb71e0a142d8f7540"], "created_at": "2026-02-13T17:41:19Z"}
{"repo": "birdnet-team/BirdNET-Analyzer", "pull_number": 881, "instance_id": "birdnet-team__BirdNET-Analyzer-881", "issue_numbers": [877], "base_commit": "59ddce6d0b30921d2158c05210a175858b81e7e0", "patch": "diff --git a/birdnet_analyzer/model.py b/birdnet_analyzer/model.py\nindex ccc08083..aeeb5e50 100644\n--- a/birdnet_analyzer/model.py\n+++ b/birdnet_analyzer/model.py\n@@ -348,18 +348,22 @@ def upsample_core(x: np.ndarray, y: np.ndarray, min_samples: int, apply, size=2)\n             x_temp.append(x_app)\n     else:\n         for i in range(y.shape[1]):\n-            while y[:, i].sum() + len(y_temp) < min_samples:\n+            class_x_temp = []\n+            class_y_temp = []\n+            while y[:, i].sum() + len(class_y_temp) < min_samples:\n                 try:\n                     # Randomly choose a sample from the minority class\n                     random_index = rng.choice(np.where(y[:, i] == 1)[0], size=size)\n                 except ValueError as e:\n                     raise get_empty_class_exception()(index=i) from e\n \n-                # Apply SMOTE\n+                # Apply\n                 x_app, y_app = apply(x, y, random_index)\n-                y_temp.append(y_app)\n-                x_temp.append(x_app)\n-\n+                class_y_temp.append(y_app)\n+                class_x_temp.append(x_app)\n+            if len(class_y_temp) > 0:\n+                x_temp.extend(class_x_temp)\n+                y_temp.extend(class_y_temp)\n     return x_temp, y_temp\n \n \n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Upsampling ratio doesn't seem to behave as the documentation suggests it would for custom model training with multiple small classes\n**Describe the bug**\n\nUpsampling ratio doesn't seem to behave as the documentation suggests it would.  For examples with large number of classes, the number of upsamples doesn't go up as fast as the clip distribution + upsampling ratio would suggest.  \n\nI *think* after upsampling the first small class, the counter (`y_temp`) inflates globally, causing subsequent classes to skip upsampling even if they're underrepresented.\n\nI think the issue is here: https://github.com/birdnet-team/BirdNET-Analyzer/blob/59ddce6d0b30921d2158c05210a175858b81e7e0/birdnet_analyzer/model.py#L351\n\nThis doesn't really have any effect for binary custom classifiers, but for a multi-class, custom model with multiple small classes, then this can make it hard to upsample them properly.\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "Hi,\nthanks for reporting this, it is indeed an error and not working as intended.\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/birdnet-team/BirdNET-Analyzer/commit/dabc5f4bc42ae6891fa79bdc5dd6dbf5984ef2dc"], "created_at": "2026-03-09T14:52:14Z"}
{"repo": "birdnet-team/BirdNET-Analyzer", "pull_number": 896, "instance_id": "birdnet-team__BirdNET-Analyzer-896", "issue_numbers": [895], "base_commit": "30cc44b8273af0a032401714f79125964711593c", "patch": "diff --git a/docs/usage/cli.rst b/docs/usage/cli.rst\nindex 590f726f9..34320fcda 100644\n--- a/docs/usage/cli.rst\n+++ b/docs/usage/cli.rst\n@@ -152,7 +152,7 @@ birdnet_analyzer.train\n    1. Collect training data and organize in folders based on species names.\n    2. Species labels should be in the format ``<scientific name>_<species common name>`` (e.g., ``Poecile atricapillus_Black-capped Chickadee``), but other formats work as well.\n    3. It can be helpful to include a non-event class. If you name a folder 'Noise', 'Background', 'Other' or 'Silence', it will be treated as a non-event class.\n-   4. Run the training script with ``python birdnet_analyzer.train <path to training data folder> -o <path to trained classifier model output>``.\n+   4. Run the training script with ``python -m birdnet_analyzer.train <path to training data folder> -o <path to trained classifier model output>``.\n \n    **The script saves the trained classifier model based on the best validation loss achieved during training. This ensures that the model saved is optimized for performance according to the chosen metric.**\n \n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Small typo in usage documentation\nThere should be `-m` in this [command](https://github.com/birdnet-team/BirdNET-Analyzer/blob/30cc44b8273af0a032401714f79125964711593c/docs/usage/cli.rst?plain=1#L155).\n\nHow it is now:\n> ...\n> Run the training script with ``python birdnet_analyzer.train <path to training data folder> -o <path to trained classifier model output>.``\n> ...\n\nFix:\n\n> ...\n> Run the training script with ``python -m birdnet_analyzer.train <path to training data folder> -o <path to trained classifier model output>.``\n> ...\n\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/birdnet-team/BirdNET-Analyzer/commit/06d55d8bc189d1af3e6b3bf90684dbf42f383fd8"], "created_at": "2026-04-21T06:12:05Z"}
